        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 8 at 4:44PM CDT by NWS Topeka KS</headline>
        <description>At 443 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a cluster of small
thunderstorms near Wells, moving southwest at 25 mph.

HAZARD...Half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Minor damage to vegetation is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Minneapolis, Bennington, Tescott, Culver, Wells, Manchester,
Longford, and Oak Hill.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
